> **CLAUDE DIRECTIVE**: STRICTLY enforce SOLID principles in ALL code generation. Violations of SRP, OCP, LSP, ISP, or DIP are CRITICAL errors.

## 1. Core Principles
Adhere to these foundational principles to ensure maintainable and extensible code. Prioritize modern C++ features for better performance and safety.

@principles_rules [
  {
    "id": "srp",
    "rule": "Single Responsibility Principle (SRP): Each class or function should have only one reason to change.",
    "severity": "high",
    "example": "Separate rendering logic from scene management to avoid bloated classes."
  },
  {
    "id": "ocp",
    "rule": "Open/Closed Principle (OCP): Classes should be open for extension but closed for modification.",
    "severity": "high",
    "example": "Use abstract base classes for renderers, allowing new implementations without changing existing code."
  },
  {
    "id": "lsp",
    "rule": "Liskov Substitution Principle (LSP): Derived classes must be substitutable for their base classes without altering program correctness.",
    "severity": "high",
    "example": "A 4D vector class deriving from a base vector should support all base operations consistently."
  },
  {
    "id": "isp",
    "rule": "Interface Segregation Principle (ISP): No client should depend on methods it doesn't use; prefer multiple small interfaces.",
    "severity": "high",
    "example": "Split a large engine interface into rendering, physics, and input interfaces."
  },
  {
    "id": "dip",
    "rule": "Dependency Inversion Principle (DIP): Depend on abstractions, not concretions; use dependency injection.",
    "severity": "high",
    "example": "Inject resource managers via interfaces rather than hardcoding concrete classes."
  },
  {
    "id": "dry",
    "rule": "DRY (Don't Repeat Yourself): Eliminate code duplication through abstraction and reuse.",
    "severity": "high",
    "example": "Use templates for common vector operations instead of repeating code for different dimensions."
  },
  {
    "id": "grasp",
    "rule": "GRASP (General Responsibility Assignment Software Patterns): Assign responsibilities to classes/objects appropriately.",
    "severity": "medium",
    "example": "Controller classes handle input, while models manage data."
  },
  {
    "id": "kiss",
    "rule": "KISS (Keep It Simple, Stupid): Prefer simple solutions over complex ones.",
    "severity": "medium",
    "example": "Use standard library algorithms instead of custom implementations unless necessary."
  },
  {
    "id": "yagni",
    "rule": "YAGNI (You Aren't Gonna Need It): Don't implement functionality until it's needed.",
    "severity": "medium",
    "example": "Avoid adding advanced 4D rotation features until required by the project."
  }
]

- Apply these principles during design reviews to maintain code quality.

## 2. Project Structure Requirements
Maintain a flat, modular structure to facilitate navigation and scalability.

@structure_rules {
  "src": "Source code implementation files",
  "include": "Header files for interfaces and declarations",
  "tests": "Unit and integration tests mirroring source structure",
  "docs": "Technical documentation and architecture diagrams",
  "examples": "Usage examples and demo applications",
  "build": "Build artifacts (add to .gitignore)",
  "scripts": "Build scripts, utilities, and automation tools",
  "config": "Configuration files for builds and runtime"
}

- Place headers and sources together for easy navigation in small projects; use subdirectories for modules in larger ones.
- Include documentation files: README.md (overview), API_Reference.md (API docs), Examples.md (tutorials), CONTRIBUTING.md (guidelines), CHANGELOG.md (history), ARCHITECTURE.md (design decisions).

## 3. Code Quality Standards
Enforce readability and maintainability through consistent practices.

@quality_rules [
  {
    "id": "file_organization",
    "rule": "One class per file (except small related classes); headers in include/ with matching sources in src/.",
    "severity": "high"
  },
  {
    "id": "naming_conventions",
    "rule": "Use PascalCase for classes, camelCase for functions and variables.",
    "severity": "high",
    "example": "class Engine4D; void renderFrame();"
  },
  {
    "id": "function_design",
    "rule": "Keep functions small (<50 lines), max 3 parameters, use meaningful names, return early.",
    "severity": "high",
    "example": "if (!valid) return; // Early return"
  },
  {
    "id": "class_design",
    "rule": "Limit classes to 200 lines, prefer composition over inheritance, use const correctness.",
    "severity": "high",
    "example": "const Vector4& getPosition() const;"
  },
  {
    "id": "error_handling",
    "rule": "Use exceptions sparingly, provide meaningful messages, never ignore errors.",
    "severity": "high",
    "example": "throw std::runtime_error(\"Invalid matrix\");"
  }
]

- Use tools like clang-tidy for static analysis and cppcheck for code quality checks.

## 4. Testing Requirements
Aim for comprehensive coverage to catch bugs early.

@testing_rules [
  {
    "id": "coverage",
    "rule": "Minimum 80% code coverage; unit tests for all public methods.",
    "severity": "high"
  },
  {
    "id": "structure",
    "rule": "Follow AAA pattern (Arrange, Act, Assert); one test per behavior.",
    "severity": "high",
    "example": "// Arrange\nint x = 1;\n// Act\nint y = addOne(x);\n// Assert\nASSERT_EQ(2, y);"
  },
  {
    "id": "tools",
    "rule": "Use frameworks like Google Test or Catch2; include sanitizers and Valgrind.",
    "severity": "medium"
  },
  {
    "id": "types",
    "rule": "Include integration, performance, and property-based tests.",
    "severity": "medium"
  }
]

- Keep tests independent; mock dependencies.

## 5. Build and CI/CD
Use CMake for cross-platform builds.

@build_rules [
  {
    "id": "system",
    "rule": "Use modern CMake (min 3.0); support Debug/Release/Profile configurations.",
    "severity": "high",
    "example": "cmake_minimum_required(VERSION 3.16)"
  },
  {
    "id": "ci",
    "rule": "Automate testing on commits; include linting, security scans.",
    "severity": "high"
  }
]

